      "span_text": "1 Following McVicar et al. [2007] , as the two regions were over 150 km inland  , the data were fit using a tri-variate partial thin plate spline, which incorporates a bi-variate thin plate spline as a function of longitude and latitude and a \"constant linear dependence on elevation.\" Other topographic and physiognomic controls such as local relative relief, local landscape shape and aspect were not utilised when determining u Z ; these were considered uniform over the 47 years.",
